ground_truth:
To add footnotes to your Latex document, you can use the command footnote{Your footnote text here}. Here's an example code that adds a footnote to a sentence:

This is a sentence with a footnote.footnote{Your footnote text here}

The footnote command will automatically number the footnotes and add them to the bottom of the page. If you want to customize the footnote numbering or appearance, you can use the "footmisc" package in your document preamble.

generated:
To add footnotes to your LaTeX document, you can use the `footnote` command. Here's a basic example:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\begin{document}

This is a sentence with a footnote\footnote{This is the footnote text.}.

\end{document}
```

However, this will place the footnote at the bottom of the page. If you want to place the footnote at the bottom of the page where the footnote marker appears, you can use the `footnote` command with an optional argument that specifies the footnote marker.

