Absolutely! To do that, you will need to modify the URL in your code to specify the country you want to retrieve data for. You can create an array of countries and then use a loop to iterate over each country and retrieve the data for that country. Here's an example code snippet that demonstrates how to do this:

$countries = array("Nigeria", "Ghana", "Kenya", "South Africa");
foreach ($countries as $country) {
 $url = "https://api.opentripmap.com/0.1/en/places/radius?radius=10000&lon=8.6753⪫=9.0820&kinds=interesting_places&limit=5&format=json&apikey=YOUR_API_KEY&country=" . urlencode($country);
 $response = file_get_contents($url);
 $data = json_decode($response, true);
 foreach ($data['features'] as $feature) {
 echo $feature['properties']['name'] . "n";
 echo $feature['properties']['description'] . "n";
 echo "![](" . $feature[)n";
 echo "Location: " . $feature['geometry']['coordinates'][1] . ", " . $feature['geometry']['coordinates'][0] . "n";
 echo "Website: " . $feature['properties']['otm_wikipedia'] . "n";
 }
}

This code will retrieve data for Nigeria, Ghana, Kenya, and South Africa, and display the top 5 tourist attractions for each country.

